{'text': 'This is just another example of how the people in this society can\'t accept anything that isn\'t "their way--and usually by that I mean whatever the oppressor wants to impose on them.'}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 There is no perfect solution for this problem. \xa0You can't just legalize drugs and expect them to disappear."}
{'text': "That might not be such a bad idea. However, it's going to take some time to get to that point. It's not going to be a quick process, but it will eventually happen."}
{'text': 'This is not about "saying no to drugs or "legalizing drugs". This is about going back to the way things were.'}
{'text': "You can legalize drugs, but you can't legalize the people who use drugs."}
{'text': "We need some sort of universal system of drug testing for everybody. It shouldn't matter where you were born or what your income level is."}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 If you want to legalize drugs, then why not legalize all drugs?'}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Remember, the government was going to legalize drugs anyway, so it doesn't really matter if they end up doing it the legal way or the illegal way."}
{'text': "We don't need to legalize drugs, we need to stop the war on drugs. It's a huge waste of resources and a huge contributor to the high rate of incarceration in this country."}
{'text': "Shouldn't we legalize drugs because they're not as harmful as they are now?"}
{'text': "Drugs are legal because they're easily available. If drugs are legal, it won't be as easy to get them."}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 The problem with legalizing drugs is that it takes away control from the people who are actually doing the drugs.'}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 The drug war is supposed to prevent people from using drugs, but it doesn't seem to work very well."}
{'text': "Drug legalization is a very interesting idea, but I'm not sure how it would actually help the majority of people that are addicted to drugs."}
{'text': 'Legalizing drugs would do nothing to lower the overall level of drug use in the United States.'}
{'text': "Some people, such as myself and my family, have a hard time accepting the idea of legalizing drugs. After all, drugs are bad, and we don't want them to be used."}
{'text': 'Legalizing drugs would make it easier for the government to regulate drugs, since the current laws regarding drugs are vague and imprecise.'}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 It is better to focus on how to get people off of drugs and not worry about the status of people who use drugs.'}
{'text': "It's not going to be that easy. The people who support the legalization of drugs are going to have to give up their current lifestyle in order to make it work."}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Either we legalize the drugs, or we don't. Either way, it's a terrible idea that has nothing to do with morality."}
{'text': "If the purpose of the war on drugs isn't to prevent drug use, then why is it still being waged?"}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 There are plenty of other drugs that are far more harmful than marijuana.'}
{'text': "Many people have tried to legalize marijuana in the US. They've failed."}
{'text': 'We really need to come to grips with the fact that drugs are dangerous, and that the current options for dealing with that danger are not going to solve the problem.'}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 If you want to have a drug-free society, then the first thing we need to do is decriminalize drugs, so that people don't go to jail for small amounts of drugs."}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 I'm not sure that decriminalization is the best way to handle this problem."}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 The US is very different from others countries in the world. Every other country has a lot of laws on the books protecting people's lives and property."}
{'text': "It's better to have a black market, than no black market at all."}
{'text': "Drugs are probably one of the biggest problems that we have in this country. There is no way that we're going to solve the problem simply by legalizing it."}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 I don't think that putting drugs out of legal reach will stop people from abusing them. I think it will likely lead to more drug abuse, and ultimately, to more drug deaths."}

{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Legalizing drugs would make the United States less of a war zone, and it would make it easier for the United States to maintain stable governments in foreign countries.'}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Since prohibition has been so ineffective, I don't know why we would do it again."}
{'text': "Are you going to legalize drugs because it's the right thing to do?"}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 In case you haven't heard, the US government is spending a lot of money to fight drugs by waging a war on drugs."}
{'text': "It would be great if we could control drug use and make sure that it doesn't lead to the spread of HIV/AIDS, but at the end of the day, I don't think it's..."}
{'text': "The fact that drugs are illegal means that they aren't used in the way they were meant to be used. This means that they don't cause the amount of harm that they are thought to cause."}
{'text': "It's probably best for the government to focus on the individuals who are actually doing the drugs, not by ignoring the problems of society as a whole."}

{'text': 'The larger government gets, the more control it gives itself over the lives of all of its citizens. \xa0 This is a bad thing because it leads to bureaucracy, corruption, and a lack of freedom.'}
{'text': 'If people were allowed to use drugs, how would we know that the drugs are safe? What happens if there is some kind of disaster, like a terrorist attack?'}
{'text': "If you legalize drugs, there will be a huge increase in the number of users. But if you can't get the users to stop using drugs, you're just setting up an even bigger problem."}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Once again, the goal of the drug war is to prevent drug use. So even if some people do get hooked on drugs, it's not the fault of the drug war."}
{'text': 'Drugs are a natural part of our society, and if we do away with them, it will cause some people to become addicted to anything other than drugs.'}
{'text': 'For everyone who supports drug legalization, take a second to take a look in the mirror.'}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Some people don't like to use drugs, don't want to deal with the effects of drugs, or simply don't want to do drugs at all."}
{'text': "It's not too late for me to change my mind about drug use. I've been using drugs for a long time now."}
{'text': 'Personally, I think that people should be able to use drugs without worrying about getting in trouble for it, which is why I support their right to do so.'}
{'text': 'There is a big difference between the idea of legalizing drugs and actually doing it.'}
{'text': "It's a good thing that we are trying to tackle this problem. I just don't think legalizing drugs is the best way to go about it."}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 I know there are a lot of people who are against legalization of drugs, but I don't think we should legalize drugs any more than we should legalize anything else."}
{'text': 'People often say that if we decriminalize drugs, then we can end the war on drugs, which I agree with.'}
{'text': "I think the prohibition of drugs was wrong from the start, and I think it's going to lead us down a path that will only end in tragedy."}
{'text': 'The idea that legalizing drugs will somehow solve the problem of drug addiction is an example of the kind of argument that has been used to justify prohibition for over a hundred years.'}
{'text': "When drugs are legal, it's not so much the drug being illegal that's the problem."}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 If marijuana were legalized in the United States, I don't know what we'd do about drug abuse, other than at the very least having more laws against drug abuse."}
{'text': 'As a society, we need to find a way to deal with drug abuse.'}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 The drug problem is big enough that marijuana should be legalized for medicinal and recreational uses.'}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 It would be very hard to enforce such laws, because there are so many people using drugs that it'd be nearly impossible to prove if someone was using drugs without a prescription."}
{'text': "My friends are right. If we legalize drugs, we'll have a big increase in users."}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 We shouldn't legalize drugs because it makes us feel good. Instead, we should legalize drugs because we know that drugs are bad, and we want them to be used in a responsible way."}
{'text': "If you legalize drugs, you are implicitly condoning the idea that drug use is not only okay but that it's good."}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 I don't think people should have to break the law in order to have a good life."}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Legalizing drugs would be a great idea, but it does not mean that we should legalize all drugs.'}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 We are so afraid of drugs that we spend billions of dollars fighting a war that doesn't seem to be working anyway."}
{'text': "There's a difference between legalization and decriminalization. If you decriminalize drugs, then criminals will start to take advantage of the law and manufacture and distribute drugs."}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 It seems obvious to me that marijuana should be decriminalized.'}
{'text': "It would be much better to legalize drugs as long as it's legal to grow them yourself. This way, you can decide for yourself if you want to use them or not."}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 If people who use drugs are treated the same as those who don't use drugs, then we won't have an issue with people who use drugs."}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 A drug user is a human being like you and me. Not all drug users are addicts. Not all addicts are drug users.'}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 What kind of society is it that kills its own children by using drugs, yet can't stop people from using them? \xa0Isn't it a contradiction?"}
{'text': "We have laws against crimes, such as rape, murder, arson, and theft. Why can't we have laws against drug crimes, such as drug abuse, addiction, and addiction-related crimes?"}
{'text': 'Is it possible to "keep our kids from using drugs"? Yes, but only if there is an active effort to make sure they don\'t get their hands on drugs.'}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 If you legalize drugs, you are implicitly condoning the idea that drug abuse is not only okay, but that it's good."}
{'text': "That being said, I don't think that legalizing drugs would cause the amount of people using drugs to go down."}
{'text': "It may not be too late to legalize drugs, but it's probably too late to make them legal. If we want to reduce the number of drug users and criminals, we need to legalize drugs."}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 To be honest, I don't think the legalization of drugs is a good idea. I don't think it will help us solve the problem of drugs in our society."}

{'text': "If you want to regulate the production and sale of drugs, you can only do so if you create a situation where people are desperate enough that they're willing to gamble their lives in order to get drugs..."}
{'text': "If we are serious about ending the war on drugs, we're going to have to put more effort into this than we already are."}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 There are some benefits to legalization, which is why I'm not opposed to it at all."}
{'text': "If you legalize drugs, you are implicitly condoning the idea that drug abuse is not only okay, but that it's good. We need to find a way to deal with drug abuse."}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 As long as drugs are illegal, there will always be a demand for them.'}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 I think it would be great if the prohibition of drugs was lifted.'}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 What if we decriminalize drugs, but only for the most serious of drugs? What happens if someone is arrested for a drug offense?'}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 As long as we continue to criminalize drugs, we'll never be able to reduce drug abuse."}
{'text': 'In order to win this war, we are going to have to put a huge amount of effort into preventing people from getting drugs in the first place.'}
{'text': "It's going to be a long time before this whole issue is resolved. And it's going to take a lot of work to get us to where we need to be."}
{'text': 'If there is no negative effect of drugs on society, then why is the prohibition of drugs still in place in the first place?'}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 We're not the first to look for a solution to this problem. Countries like Sweden, Holland, and Portugal have shown that it's possible to legalize drugs without causing any problems."}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 If you legalize drugs, you are likely to see a rise in the number of people addicted to them.'}
{'text': 'When you legalize something, you open the door to all kinds of abuse and criminal activity.'}
{'text': 'Would you rather have 3.5 billion people smoking 5.4 billion cigarettes or 100 million people using illegal drugs?'}
{'text': 'If we are going to legalize drugs, we have to eliminate all the problems with the current system. In particular, we have to figure out how to educate people on the dangers of drug use.'}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 When you decide to decriminalize drugs, you do so at your own peril. You are taking a risk.'}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 I think it would be much better to legalize drugs as long as it's legal to grow them yourself."}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 The war on drugs is nothing more than a continuation of the war on blacks.'}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 No matter how big the problem is, it's never going to be solved simply by making drugs legal."}
